cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the performance of interweave cognitive radio systems, which involves signal processing, communication networks, and system engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with spectrum sensing, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses interference avoidance, which is a key aspect of cognitive radio systems, and hence, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a novel approach to incorporate channel estimation, which is related to system modeling and control, and hence, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the achievable secondary throughput, which is related to multimedia systems, and hence, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
